               <dir-section id="BG.DIR.231" id-root="bg.dir" iso="bg" sect-type="religion" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="DIR-SECTREF" usage="ewyb casee">
                    <heading>Religion</heading>
                    <p id="BG.DIR.232">Most of the population professes Christianity, the main denomination being the Bulgarian Orthodox Church. There are also small communities of Protestants, Roman Catholics (including adherents of Byzantine rites) and Armenian Orthodox. The 1991 Constitution guarantees freedom of religion, although Eastern Orthodox Christianity is declared to be the traditional religion in Bulgaria’.</p>
                    <p>At the 2021 census, 71.5% of the population who responded to the question on religious denomination identified themselves as Christian, with 97.0% of the total being adherents of the Bulgarian Orthodox Church. Most of the Muslim population of Bulgaria are ethnic Turks, and 10.8% of the population described themselves as Muslim in 2021. There are some ethnic Bulgarian Muslims, known as Pomaks. There is a small Jewish community.</p>
                    <!--MR 22.11.2023 https://nsi.bg/sites/default/files/files/pressreleases/Census2021_ethnos.pdf-->
